To analyze a suspicious API request, you can use Postman to simulate the request and analyze the response. Here's an example:
```javascript
// Load the API request in Postman
var request = new XMLHttpRequest();
request.open("GET", "https://api.example.com/data", true);
request.onload = function() {
    var response = request.responseText;
    console.log(response);
}
request.send();
```
Common Postman features used for API analysis include:

* `GET`, `POST`, `PUT`, `DELETE` methods to simulate API requests
* `Authorization` headers to authenticate API requests
* `Headers` tab to view and modify API request headers
* `Body` tab to view and modify API request bodies

